The chart bellow shows how different packages relate to each other in terms of their bytecode size or a total number of their methods.

Breakdown type represents a metric used for calculating every package percentage. Available metrics are: method bytecode size, and method count.

Object types Count Size in total
Module
  • Shows the resource module
  • Entries marked as unnamed are not from module
 Name
  • Shows the resource name
  • Number in the brackets represents number of different resources with same name and module values
 Count
  • Shows the number of occurrences for the particular resource.
  • A number greater than one can indicate a problem, because it means that a resource was embedded multiple times
 Origin
  • Shows the resource location on the system
  • Entries marked as Injected were added programmatically
  • Browsers cannot open all types of resources (e.g. jars)

  • Shows the resource type
    • : directory resource
    • : file resource
    • : missing resource - was tried to be registered but does not exist on the system

  • Shows the resource size
  • The size of directory resources depends on the size of all directory entry names
